The Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) in Ekiti State has sympathised with the State Governor, Dr Kayode Fayemi, who just confirmed that he has contracted COVID-19. The party through the Secretary of the State Caretaker Committee, Prince Diran Odeyemi, wished the governor quick recovery, urging those around him to isolate themselves and undergo COVID-19 test too. Odeyemi who said testing positive for coronavirus was not a death sentence, adding that Governor Fayemi will surely recover and come out negative. The party urged Ekiti people to keep faith with the COVID-19 precautionary measures outlined by Governor Fayemi’s administration, bearing in mind that the virus is real and yet to have any cure. “As a party, we wish the governor well. We pray that he recovers quickly. “We also wish to call on our people in the length and breadth of Ekiti State to continue to observe the COVID-19 protocols so as to keep low the rate of infection in the State,” Odeyemi said.